The paper discusses the use of Formal Concept Analysis (FCA) to extract conceptual knowledge from Wikidata, which is a large and complex knowledge graph. FCA is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB) for knowledge representation and data analysis. The paper also mentions experiments and results, which suggest the use of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and semantic web (cs.SI) techniques.
